//
// T030 — R5 operator spacing per formatting-rules.contract.md §5.
//
// Frozen invariants:
//   * binary operators get one space on each side
//   * unary operators get no space between operator and operand
//   * conditional `?` `:` operators get one space around each
//
// AUTHORED RED per Principle VIII TDD discipline; expected-fail
// marker below until T049 implements R5 in lib/Fmt/LayoutPlanner.cpp.
// Today's byte-passthrough formatter emits the input as-is; the
// CHECK pattern below expects canonical spacing. When the rule
// implementation lands, the test must turn GREEN and the
// expected-fail marker must be REMOVED in the same change.

// `reg` (not `wire`) is used for the initialized declarations
// because S2 forbids `wire <name> = <init>` (use `reg` instead).
// XFAIL: *
// RUN: echo 'module m { reg x[8] = a+b; reg y[8] = ~c; }' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: reg x[8] = a + b;
// CHECK: reg y[8] = ~c;
